## Daily Memory - 2026-03-09

- **PulsarWebDriver click test realignment:** Replaced the disabled `PulsarWebDriverClickTests` coverage that still targeted the old dynamic page with active E2E tests against `generated/interactive-screens.html`, using current selectors like `#addButton` and `#toggleMessageButton`. The new suite now validates count-based clicks, modifier clicks, no-op missing-element clicks, disabled-button behavior, navigation, and sequential interactions that match the live page structure. **Learning:** When generated mock pages evolve, refresh test fixtures against the real HTML instead of preserving stale selectors; for Browser4 E2E classes tagged `E2ETest`, remember to enable them with `-DrunE2ETests=true` or Maven will report zero executed tests.

- **Validation outcome:** Verified the rewritten class with `./mvnw.cmd -f pulsar-tests\\pom.xml -pl pulsar-it-tests -am -DrunE2ETests=true -Dtest=PulsarWebDriverClickTests -D"surefire.failIfNoSpecifiedTests=false" test`, which finished with 13 tests run, 0 failures, 0 errors. **Learning:** Sequential click tests on this page are more reliable when assertions reflect actual current page behavior (for example, the calculator button can legitimately produce the validation message when fields are not populated in the interaction flow being tested).


